On behalf of the entire Camden-Frontier community of students, parents, staff, faculty and the board of education, our best wishes and sincerest thanks go out to Cynthia Moore for her 38 years of service to our students and Donna Shaneour for her 21 years of service. Both officially retire on June 30.

As an elementary teacher, Mrs. Moore created a warm and nurturing classroom environment with high expectations for kindness and achievement. Her first students, now in their mid-40's, and her last all benefited greatly from her dedication, hard work and professionalism. Although she will be greatly missed at C-F by colleagues and students alike, we wish Mrs. Moore the happiest of retirements. It is well deserved!

Working in our Food Service Department, Donna Shaneour has demonstrated how every member of the C-F staff contributes to our children's education. Anyone who knows Donna knows that few people work harder. She has been an outstanding example of dedication and hard work to all of our students for over two decades. We wish her the best.

post_text: Spread the news! Graduation events for the Class of 2020 have been rescheduled! Commencement will take place on the football field in the cool 10 am morning air on Saturday, July 25. The field provides abundant room for social distancing so we can conduct as traditional a ceremony as possible with an unlimited audience. In the event of rain, we have not one but two make-up opportunities: the first is 4 pm the same day and the second is 2 pm the following day, Sunday July 26. In a worst-case scenario, the event would be moved to the gym with limited attendance consistent with state requirements at the time. To all that will continue to participate in sports in one way or another, please continue practicing safe social distancing but also if safe, continue to prepare and work for the upcoming seasons.

Stay safe Redskins Nation.

We are happy to announce that Camden-Frontier will be establishing three food distribution points for our students beginning this Thursday, March 19, from 3:00 to 5:30 pm or until supplies run out.

All C-F students are eligible to pick up one bag of breakfast and lunch foods. Each bag will contain approximately 5 meals. We will be distributing food from these locations:

School (follow the signs to the cafeteria)
Camden Missionary Church (look for the bus)
Montgomery & Steamburg in Frontier (look for the bus)

We will offer the same service on Tuesday and Thursday of next week, March 24 and 26.

If the school closure is extended beyond April 5, we plan to continue and expand food service to our students.

If you would like to donate to this food program - either whole foods like fruits and vegetables or pre-packaged foods like granola bars, cheese, sticks, etc. - please message us. Cash donations of any/all sizes are also welcome. Our community is in need and we need your help. Please share.
